      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Their main objection will be that affirmative action policies unfairly Advantage group-based quotas over Individual merit, essentially rewarding unqualified candidates for group membership rather than qualifications. They'll argue that a race-blind approach ensures that hiring and promotions are based solely on merit, combating biases and stereotypes. By eliminating quotas and diversity mandates, they claim that employers can rely on objective criteria to select the best candidates, making the hiring process truly fair. This approach also acknowledges the existance of long-eliminated systemic inequality, not caused by intent. Those who advocate for quotas will inevitably be silenced by the \"colorblind\" approach.",
      "source": "target",
